1
00:00:01,044 --> 00:00:03,797
<i>Previously on</i> Lucifer...
I wasn't lying.

2
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:06,007
I do intend to use
the Flaming Sword

3
00:00:06,216 --> 00:00:07,384
to cut through
the Gates of Heaven.

4
00:00:07,592 --> 00:00:08,551
But what you left out?

5
00:00:08,760 --> 00:00:10,595
I plan on kicking Mum
into Heaven

6
00:00:10,804 --> 00:00:12,681
<i>and slamming the gates
on her backside.</i>

7
00:00:12,889 --> 00:00:15,225
Maybe there's
another piece missing.
MOM: <i>If you find the killer,</i>

8
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,060
<i>then you'll find our piece of the Flaming Sword.</i>

9
00:00:17,268 --> 00:00:18,603
I went through a
lot this last year,

10
00:00:18,812 --> 00:00:20,897
and improv sort of helped
me reorient myself.

11
00:00:21,106 --> 00:00:22,023
LUCIFER: Amenadiel
told you about our trip

12
00:00:22,232 --> 00:00:23,274
back to Heaven,
didn't he?

13
00:00:23,483 --> 00:00:25,860
(shouts)
<i>You</i> should have told me.

14
00:00:26,236 --> 00:00:29,030
- As promised.
- This opens a
safety deposit box.

15
00:00:29,531 --> 00:00:31,866
LAPD. Bianca Ruiz,
you're under arrest.

16
00:00:32,075 --> 00:00:35,412
Are you certain this is all that
was in the safety deposit box?

17
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:37,122
We'll fix it.
There's plenty of time.

18
00:00:37,372 --> 00:00:38,415
MOM:
<i>Just not for me.</i>

19
00:00:38,623 --> 00:00:41,584
God shattered the Flaming Sword
into three distinct pieces.

20
00:00:41,793 --> 00:00:43,586
The Blade of Death,
the Medallion of Life

21
00:00:43,795 --> 00:00:45,588
and the Key that binds
them all together.

22
00:00:45,797 --> 00:00:46,923
Look down.

23
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:50,135
He entrusted
it to you.

24
00:00:50,343 --> 00:00:51,886
Congrats on nabbing
Queen Tequila.

25
00:00:52,095 --> 00:00:53,263
Well, Chet's still out there,

26
00:00:53,471 --> 00:00:54,556
<i>so this isn't over.</i>

27
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:56,433
I need what
Zeke really smuggled.

28
00:00:56,641 --> 00:00:57,934
(grunts)

29
00:00:58,143 --> 00:00:59,352
My life is ruined!

30
00:01:04,899 --> 00:01:06,276
(panting)

31
00:01:09,362 --> 00:01:10,196
(metal clicks)

32
00:01:10,405 --> 00:01:11,906
(Mom groans)

33
00:01:13,575 --> 00:01:14,367
(metal clicks)

34
00:01:14,576 --> 00:01:16,077
(Mom groans)

35
00:01:16,286 --> 00:01:17,871
(metal clicking)

36
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:21,708
♪♪ Lonely shadows
following me... ♪♪

37
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:22,876
Ow.

38
00:01:23,084 --> 00:01:26,087
♪♪ Lonely ghosts come a-callin' ♪♪

39
00:01:27,047 --> 00:01:30,884
♪♪ Lonely voices talking to me ♪♪

40
00:01:31,092 --> 00:01:34,179
♪♪ Now I'm gone, now I'm gone,
now I'm gone ♪♪

41
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:37,640
♪♪ And my mother told me ♪♪

42
00:01:37,849 --> 00:01:40,018
♪♪ Son, let it be ♪♪

43
00:01:40,226 --> 00:01:42,896
♪♪ Sold my soul
to the calling... ♪♪

44
00:01:43,104 --> 00:01:44,481
(sighs)

45
00:01:44,689 --> 00:01:46,649
♪♪ Sold my soul to... ♪♪

46
00:01:47,317 --> 00:01:48,234
Hello?

47
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:50,320
It's Charlotte Richards.

48
00:01:50,904 --> 00:01:52,280
I need a favor.

49
00:01:53,031 --> 00:01:55,116
♪♪ Oh, gimme that fire ♪♪

50
00:01:55,325 --> 00:01:57,077
<i>♪♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪♪</i>

51
00:01:57,285 --> 00:01:59,245
♪♪ Oh, gimme that fire ♪♪

52
00:01:59,454 --> 00:02:01,331
<i>♪♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪♪</i>

53
00:02:01,539 --> 00:02:02,749
♪♪ Oh, gimme that. ♪♪

54
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:05,168
Would you look at that, Luci?

55
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:07,796
It really is
the final piece.

56
00:02:08,171 --> 00:02:09,297
Unbelievable.

57
00:02:09,464 --> 00:02:11,132
- Oh, no, I believe it.
- (pours drink)

58
00:02:11,341 --> 00:02:12,759
It's classic Dad.

59
00:02:13,009 --> 00:02:14,886
Hanging the final piece
of the Flaming Sword

60
00:02:15,095 --> 00:02:16,930
right under our noses--
well...

61
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,098
your nose,

62
00:02:18,306 --> 00:02:19,849
(laughs):
this entire time.

63
00:02:20,058 --> 00:02:21,684
(both laugh)

64
00:02:21,893 --> 00:02:22,936
I know, right?

65
00:02:23,144 --> 00:02:24,521
(laughs)
It's ridiculous.

66
00:02:24,729 --> 00:02:26,606
I mean, if that isn't
the biggest celestial bird

67
00:02:26,815 --> 00:02:28,066
Dad's ever flipped.

68
00:02:29,109 --> 00:02:30,193
What are you talking about?

69
00:02:31,903 --> 00:02:34,155
This means that
I'm the favorite son.

70
00:02:34,364 --> 00:02:37,659
Uh, no, it means that once again

71
00:02:37,826 --> 00:02:41,037
Dad is manipulating us
six ways to Sunday.

72
00:02:41,246 --> 00:02:42,914
But, hey, what's new?

73
00:02:43,331 --> 00:02:44,624
At least we have it now.

74
00:02:45,416 --> 00:02:46,126
So...

75
00:02:52,006 --> 00:02:52,757
Well, hand it over, Brother.

76
00:02:52,966 --> 00:02:54,634
The sword's not
gonna ignite itself.

77
00:02:56,469 --> 00:02:58,805
It... oh, just
give it to me.

78
00:02:59,305 --> 00:03:01,474
Give it to me. Right,
don't be silly, Brother.

79
00:03:01,683 --> 00:03:02,934
You know I'm ten times
stronger than you.

80
00:03:03,143 --> 00:03:04,435
But I'm the favorite.

81
00:03:04,978 --> 00:03:06,646
Oh, right. Of course.

82
00:03:06,855 --> 00:03:07,730
(laughs) That one.

83
00:03:10,275 --> 00:03:12,193
Right, don't
make me hurt you.

84
00:03:12,402 --> 00:03:13,862
Remember, you're not
the angel you once were.

85
00:03:16,406 --> 00:03:18,491
No, Luci, you're
right, I'm not.

86
00:03:19,117 --> 00:03:20,451
Well, oh.

87
00:03:21,286 --> 00:03:22,704
I didn't mean to make you
all broody again.

88
00:03:22,912 --> 00:03:23,872
No, it's okay.

89
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:26,708
I just need a little time to
process what it all means.

90
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:28,042
Process?

91
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:30,587
Okay. Fine.

92
00:03:30,795 --> 00:03:32,338
Suppose we're
in no real rush.

93
00:03:32,547 --> 00:03:34,048
Process away.

94
00:03:35,383 --> 00:03:36,968
I think I've got <i>E.T.</i> on the DVR

95
00:03:37,177 --> 00:03:37,969
if you need a good weep

96
00:03:38,178 --> 00:03:40,805
and a pint of Häagen-Dazs
in the freezer if that helps.

97
00:03:41,014 --> 00:03:42,515
♪♪♪♪

98
00:03:56,237 --> 00:03:56,863
(gasps)

99
00:03:58,656 --> 00:04:01,451
You scared me. God!

100
00:04:02,285 --> 00:04:03,494
Goddess.

101
00:04:04,370 --> 00:04:05,121
But whatever.

102
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:06,789
I need medical attention.

103
00:04:07,332 --> 00:04:08,208
I'm wounded.

104
00:04:08,416 --> 00:04:10,043
Then go to a hospital.

105
00:04:10,293 --> 00:04:13,713
This isn't exactly
a human injury,

106
00:04:13,922 --> 00:04:15,506
and since you know who,

107
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:18,218
or rather what I am,

108
00:04:18,676 --> 00:04:21,596
I would appreciate it
if you would just patch me up.

109
00:04:21,804 --> 00:04:23,932
Why does everybody
keep doing this to me?

110
00:04:24,474 --> 00:04:25,767
I am a doctor,

111
00:04:25,975 --> 00:04:28,311
but patching people up
isn't my thing.

112
00:04:28,645 --> 00:04:29,312
Oh.

113
00:04:31,856 --> 00:04:34,275
It is now.

114
00:04:35,735 --> 00:04:37,153
Suppose I could
take a gander.

115
00:04:37,987 --> 00:04:39,155
Wonderful.

116
00:04:42,992 --> 00:04:45,620
I should warn you,
you might have to...

117
00:04:45,828 --> 00:04:46,955
(gasps)

118
00:04:49,415 --> 00:04:50,959
- ...duck.
- What?!

119
00:04:51,793 --> 00:04:52,585
Who did that to you?

120
00:04:52,794 --> 00:04:54,963
I mean, was it Lucifer?

121
00:04:56,005 --> 00:04:56,673
I-I mean...

122
00:04:56,881 --> 00:04:58,925
(laughs nervously)

123
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,677
...not on purpose, you know.

124
00:05:00,885 --> 00:05:02,512
Accidentally,
like with that

125
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,138
Flaming Sword thingy.

126
00:05:04,806 --> 00:05:05,723
(chuckles)

127
00:05:05,932 --> 00:05:07,267
All right, let me see
what I got here.

128
00:05:14,357 --> 00:05:15,441
Okay, duct tape.

129
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,111
Trust me.

130
00:05:19,654 --> 00:05:20,863
This stuff's amazing.

131
00:05:21,072 --> 00:05:25,451
♪♪ Slow burn ♪♪

132
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:26,828
♪♪ Push it out right. ♪♪

133
00:05:27,036 --> 00:05:28,621
This is ridiculous.

134
00:05:29,205 --> 00:05:30,039
You have experience

135
00:05:30,248 --> 00:05:31,582
with emotionally fragile men,
don't you?

136
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:33,042
You're self-aware today.

137
00:05:33,584 --> 00:05:34,335
No, I meant Dan.

138
00:05:34,544 --> 00:05:35,795
Anyway, tell me,

139
00:05:36,004 --> 00:05:38,047
how do you stop them
from overthinking everything?

140
00:05:38,631 --> 00:05:39,549
Who's overthinking?

141
00:05:39,757 --> 00:05:40,717
Amenadiel.

142
00:05:41,384 --> 00:05:42,468
Leave it to him
to turn a compliment

143
00:05:42,677 --> 00:05:44,304
into something
to angst over.

144
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:46,806
I mean, he should be happy
he's Dad's favorite.

145
00:05:47,682 --> 00:05:49,976
Wait, your dad didn't actually
tell you guys that, did he?

146
00:05:50,351 --> 00:05:53,354
Well, in so many
Sumerian words, yes.

147
00:05:54,105 --> 00:05:57,191
You know, the more
I hear about your dad,

148
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,235
the more I understand
why you're...

149
00:06:00,695 --> 00:06:01,571
you know, you.

150
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:03,239
ELLA:
Body dump.

151
00:06:03,448 --> 00:06:06,326
Weird one, too, and not just
'cause of the obvious

152
00:06:06,534 --> 00:06:08,494
buck naked, deep-fried
head thing.

153
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:13,624
But someone also shaved
this poor guy's entire body.

154
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,210
- Hmm.
- Well, maybe our poor killer's
just chaetophobic.

155
00:06:17,128 --> 00:06:17,920
Fear of hair.

156
00:06:18,379 --> 00:06:19,714
Always fun when
they turn up in Hell.

157
00:06:20,089 --> 00:06:21,215
Lots of wigs involved.

158
00:06:23,551 --> 00:06:25,011
But I'm pretty sure...

159
00:06:26,137 --> 00:06:27,180
(sniffs)

160
00:06:27,472 --> 00:06:29,015
...this guy got a bath
in bleach.

161
00:06:29,223 --> 00:06:30,516
CHLOE: So, whoever
dumped him is a pro.

162
00:06:30,725 --> 00:06:33,603
- It's like he just vanished off
the face of the Earth.
- ELLA: I know.

163
00:06:33,936 --> 00:06:36,981
But it's pretty tough for
someone to cover every track.

164
00:06:37,398 --> 00:06:39,484
If anyone can find something,
it's you, Ella.

165
00:06:39,692 --> 00:06:41,527
Aw, that is so sweet!

166
00:06:41,986 --> 00:06:43,029
LUCIFER: Yes, well,
u-until you do,

167
00:06:43,237 --> 00:06:45,365
I've got some personal business
I need to tend to.

168
00:06:46,532 --> 00:06:48,242
'Cause, you know, you're not
so much with the nice words,

169
00:06:48,451 --> 00:06:49,410
but when they come out...

170
00:06:52,497 --> 00:06:53,664
(knocks on door)

171
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:55,583
(sighs)

172
00:06:56,834 --> 00:06:57,877
- Doctor.
- Hi.

173
00:06:58,086 --> 00:07:00,296
Lucifer, what's up?

174
00:07:00,505 --> 00:07:02,006
I'm wondering if
you've seen Amenadiel.

175
00:07:02,215 --> 00:07:02,882
Nope.

176
00:07:03,091 --> 00:07:06,386
Haven't seen <i>that</i> family member. No.

177
00:07:06,594 --> 00:07:08,262
Can you stop being weird
and just let me in?

178
00:07:10,098 --> 00:07:10,765
Mum.

179
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:13,351
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, you know,

180
00:07:14,435 --> 00:07:15,478
girl stuff.

181
00:07:16,062 --> 00:07:18,189
LUCIFER: (chuckles)
Naked girl stuff?

182
00:07:18,689 --> 00:07:20,066
Dr. Linda, I had no idea.

183
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:22,443
(laughs)

184
00:07:22,652 --> 00:07:23,486
What is that?

185
00:07:28,699 --> 00:07:30,785
All right,
out with it, Mother.

186
00:07:31,452 --> 00:07:32,662
It's nothing.

187
00:07:33,454 --> 00:07:34,455
That spoiled brat,

188
00:07:34,664 --> 00:07:35,915
Chet Ruiz, stabbed me,

189
00:07:36,124 --> 00:07:36,999
and now I'm bleeding light.

190
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:39,293
It's... it's no big deal.

191
00:07:39,794 --> 00:07:40,878
What?

192
00:07:41,087 --> 00:07:42,422
That's a huge deal.

193
00:07:43,172 --> 00:07:44,924
Mum, if your powers are
returning to this degree,

194
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,635
then your human body won't be
able to contain it, you'll...

195
00:07:48,511 --> 00:07:49,387
you'll burst.

196
00:07:49,804 --> 00:07:50,430
Oh, no.

197
00:07:50,638 --> 00:07:51,973
I need to find Amenadiel now.

198
00:07:52,181 --> 00:07:53,141
I'd rather you didn't.

199
00:07:53,766 --> 00:07:54,809
I mean, it's bad enough

200
00:07:55,017 --> 00:07:56,644
- that you'll be worried.
- No, that's just it, Mum.

201
00:07:56,853 --> 00:07:59,063
Amenadiel has the missing
piece of the sword.

202
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,982
You're k... you're kidding.

203
00:08:01,524 --> 00:08:03,776
Son, why didn't
you say something?

204
00:08:04,318 --> 00:08:07,530
Now we can finally ignite it and
cut through the Gates of Heaven

205
00:08:07,738 --> 00:08:12,160
and I can see my... I can...
I can see my children.

206
00:08:13,077 --> 00:08:16,539
Yes. Yes, but for now,
I need to find Amenadiel

207
00:08:16,747 --> 00:08:18,458
and you need
to stay away from humans.

208
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,460
You're a... ticking bomb.

209
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,462
Uh, um, actually,

210
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:26,841
speaking of that, I...
may have already

211
00:08:27,508 --> 00:08:30,303
harmed... someone.

212
00:08:32,472 --> 00:08:33,473
Oh, no.

213
00:08:33,681 --> 00:08:34,307
No, no, no.

214
00:08:34,515 --> 00:08:36,893
I just came from a crime scene--
the man with a burned head.

215
00:08:37,101 --> 00:08:38,603
Please tell me that isn't Chet.

216
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:40,855
The detective
is on that case.

217
00:08:41,063 --> 00:08:43,149
Well, not to worry.
I had a pro clean up the mess.

218
00:08:43,357 --> 00:08:44,358
You don't understand.

219
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:47,236
The detective is good,
annoyingly good.

220
00:08:47,445 --> 00:08:49,906
Well, then we just need
to find Amenadiel, don't we?

221
00:08:50,114 --> 00:08:51,824
- Yes.
- And get the piece.

222
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,326
Because if we don't
get you back to Heaven

223
00:08:53,534 --> 00:08:54,869
before the detective
gets to you,

224
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:58,372
then she is quite
literally toast.

225
00:08:59,957 --> 00:09:00,666
(sighs)

226
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:02,710
♪♪♪♪

227
00:09:16,057 --> 00:09:17,892
Did you slip
on a banana peel, too?

228
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,228
- What?
- I'm afraid you're
gonna need surgery.

229
00:09:21,646 --> 00:09:22,313
Don't fight it.

230
00:09:22,522 --> 00:09:23,439
The kid's fierce.

231
00:09:23,898 --> 00:09:24,690
I...

232
00:09:25,816 --> 00:09:27,401
So, I left Mum
in the wine cellar at Lux,

233
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:29,195
and that's the situation.

234
00:09:29,487 --> 00:09:30,488
(inhales sharply)
Ouch.

235
00:09:30,696 --> 00:09:31,656
Baby.

236
00:09:32,532 --> 00:09:33,824
I still don't get
why you're here.

237
00:09:34,033 --> 00:09:36,953
Because I need the best
bounty hunter out there.

238
00:09:37,161 --> 00:09:37,954
I can deal
with the detective,

239
00:09:38,162 --> 00:09:39,539
but I need you
to find Amenadiel.

240
00:09:39,705 --> 00:09:41,457
Then we can get the pendant,
assemble the sword

241
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,459
before Mum spews
light everywhere.

242
00:09:43,668 --> 00:09:45,044
You don't have
to speak in code.

243
00:09:45,253 --> 00:09:47,046
I can handle adult stuff.

244
00:09:47,255 --> 00:09:48,881
MAZE: So what if
your mother explodes?

245
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:50,174
Why should I care?

246
00:09:50,383 --> 00:09:53,719
Because many, many humans
could get hurt.

247
00:09:53,928 --> 00:09:54,554
Yeah, and?

248
00:09:54,762 --> 00:09:56,430
Oh, nice try, Maze,
but I happen to know

249
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:58,432
there's a few
that you care about.

250
00:10:00,434 --> 00:10:01,519
Fine.

251
00:10:02,645 --> 00:10:03,771
But you pay me
my standard fee.

252
00:10:03,938 --> 00:10:04,814
No freebies.

253
00:10:05,022 --> 00:10:06,065
Absolutely.

254
00:10:06,941 --> 00:10:07,567
Oh.

255
00:10:07,817 --> 00:10:09,068
Love me a lolli.

256
00:10:10,069 --> 00:10:12,196
Sorry, wussies don't get any.

257
00:10:16,742 --> 00:10:18,911
♪♪♪♪

258
00:10:19,078 --> 00:10:22,081
♪♪ My night is day, yeah... ♪♪

259
00:10:23,499 --> 00:10:24,584
So, I ran the prints,

260
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:28,170
and it came back as
your brother Chet.

261
00:10:30,172 --> 00:10:31,299
I'm sorry.

262
00:10:33,009 --> 00:10:33,801
I know that you've been

263
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:37,513
living in Mexico,
but can you think of anyone

264
