No!

516
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,378
Regardless of whether
you're with Mom or not,

517
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:13,422
I simply can't
let Mom loose on Dad.

518
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:15,591
Now, it is finally
time that I go back

519
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:18,385
to being the loyal soldier
that he entrusted me to be.

520
00:20:19,219 --> 00:20:20,429
Mom is not
going anywhere!

521
00:20:20,637 --> 00:20:23,640
Well, I am afraid that we do not
have a choice, Brother!

522
00:20:23,932 --> 00:20:25,601
Mum's powers
are returning,

523
00:20:25,809 --> 00:20:27,686
and it won't be long
before we can't contain them.

524
00:20:27,895 --> 00:20:29,354
I mean, she's already
killed one person,

525
00:20:29,563 --> 00:20:31,023
and now the detective is on a...

526
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:34,234
the detective is on her case.

527
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,403
So, please,
no discussion.

528
00:20:36,945 --> 00:20:38,572
- Mum has to go!
- (elevator bell dings)

529
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:41,116
MAZE:
She already has.

530
00:20:43,285 --> 00:20:44,369
Your mother's gone.

531
00:20:46,538 --> 00:20:47,164
What?

532
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:50,417
MOM: It's Cheval
something or other.

533
00:20:50,751 --> 00:20:53,086
It's valuable,
so it must be good.

534
00:20:57,424 --> 00:20:59,384
I wasn't expecting to see you

535
00:20:59,635 --> 00:21:01,136
or your...
(chuckles)

536
00:21:01,345 --> 00:21:03,305
deadly light back so soon.

537
00:21:03,513 --> 00:21:05,140
Well, something's
been bothering me.

538
00:21:05,682 --> 00:21:07,809
When you first
saw my wound...

539
00:21:08,602 --> 00:21:10,187
you asked if Lucifer
had done it.

540
00:21:11,063 --> 00:21:12,481
What did you
mean by that?

541
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:14,066
I meant nothing by it.

542
00:21:14,274 --> 00:21:15,234
(chuckles):
You know?

543
00:21:15,651 --> 00:21:17,819
Meaningless brain fart,
you know?

544
00:21:18,028 --> 00:21:20,155
Just blah. Came out.

545
00:21:21,281 --> 00:21:22,366
There was a lot
going on that day.

546
00:21:22,574 --> 00:21:23,325
Hmm.

547
00:21:24,534 --> 00:21:26,078
I don't think so.

548
00:21:27,287 --> 00:21:29,456
I think, in fact,

549
00:21:29,665 --> 00:21:31,124
that you know something.

550
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:33,001
I don't want to
hurt you, Linda.

551
00:21:33,377 --> 00:21:35,879
I... am running...

552
00:21:36,463 --> 00:21:37,756
out of time.

553
00:21:38,298 --> 00:21:40,634
You've seen what's
happening to me.

554
00:21:40,842 --> 00:21:44,304
So you can either
tell me what you know

555
00:21:44,805 --> 00:21:46,473
over a glass of wine

556
00:21:46,723 --> 00:21:50,978
or over your own
charbroiled corpse.

557
00:21:51,436 --> 00:21:52,604
Your choice.

558
00:21:56,942 --> 00:21:58,902
I came here to grill
Kathleen on the false alibi.

559
00:22:00,612 --> 00:22:03,282
DAN: Whoa. Somebody
already had, huh?

560
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:04,866
Yeah.

561
00:22:05,075 --> 00:22:06,076
It's Ava Lyon.

562
00:22:06,618 --> 00:22:08,036
I'm thinking whoever killed Chet

563
00:22:08,287 --> 00:22:10,414
hired the Lyon sisters
to clean up,

564
00:22:10,622 --> 00:22:11,748
then cleaned up the cleaner.

565
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:13,792
Excuse me, what is going on?

566
00:22:14,001 --> 00:22:14,918
I work here.

567
00:22:16,211 --> 00:22:17,045
Ava!

568
00:22:18,380 --> 00:22:19,047
Stop.

569
00:22:19,256 --> 00:22:21,216
(crying):
Oh, my God.

570
00:22:22,175 --> 00:22:24,136
What did I do?

571
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:26,722
KATHLEEN:
<i>It's me, only me.</i>

572
00:22:27,431 --> 00:22:29,433
Ava knew nothing about it.

573
00:22:30,934 --> 00:22:32,477
I wasn't lying about Brad.

574
00:22:33,437 --> 00:22:34,896
I did get back
together with him,

575
00:22:35,105 --> 00:22:38,734
but he gambles a lot,
and he needed money.

576
00:22:39,568 --> 00:22:43,864
Then I got this call
offering me a hundred grand.

577
00:22:47,284 --> 00:22:48,618
Who hired you?

578
00:22:48,827 --> 00:22:50,829
Who killed Chet and your sister?

579
00:22:51,371 --> 00:22:53,332
Maybe Ava's death was a warning.

580
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,585
For me to keep
my mouth shut.

581
00:22:56,793 --> 00:22:58,295
Maybe if I don't say anything...

582
00:22:59,171 --> 00:23:00,213
(sighs)

583
00:23:04,634 --> 00:23:06,178
So how do we find Mom?

584
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:08,347
Follow the trail
of roasted humans?

585
00:23:08,555 --> 00:23:10,932
Well, if anyone can find
that wily goddess, it's Maze.

586
00:23:11,141 --> 00:23:13,477
- She's on it.
- (phone ringing)

587
00:23:16,396 --> 00:23:17,981
Detective.
Everything all right?

588
00:23:18,190 --> 00:23:18,857
CHLOE:
We found a body.

589
00:23:19,066 --> 00:23:19,733
Another body?

590
00:23:19,941 --> 00:23:20,567
A burned head.

591
00:23:20,776 --> 00:23:22,611
- Same burned head?
- CHLOE: Yes.

592
00:23:22,819 --> 00:23:24,905
So, what, you think whoever
killed Chet killed again?

593
00:23:25,113 --> 00:23:27,032
Look, Lucifer,
it's a long story,

594
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:29,034
but the second victim
is Ava Lyon.

595
00:23:29,242 --> 00:23:30,827
She's one of
the cleaners we met.

596
00:23:31,036 --> 00:23:32,454
I have her sister Kathleen here,

597
00:23:32,662 --> 00:23:34,373
but she's not saying anything--
she's scared.

598
00:23:34,581 --> 00:23:36,124
So I need you to come here,

599
00:23:36,291 --> 00:23:38,043
and I need you to do
your mojo thing.

600
00:23:38,335 --> 00:23:41,254
Yes, Detective,
believe me when I say

601
00:23:41,421 --> 00:23:43,715
I want to find the killer
as much as you do.

602
00:23:43,924 --> 00:23:44,966
Hello, boys.

603
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:46,093
Mum.

604
00:23:46,301 --> 00:23:47,677
What? What? What's going on?

605
00:23:47,886 --> 00:23:49,971
I-I'm so sorry. My mum's here.

606
00:23:50,180 --> 00:23:51,139
I-I've got to rush.

607
00:23:51,348 --> 00:23:53,892
Good luck with
Kathleen. Ciao.

608
00:23:54,101 --> 00:23:55,352
Damn it.

609
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:56,520
- What's wrong?
- Lucifer.

610
00:23:56,728 --> 00:23:57,813
He's...

611
00:23:58,397 --> 00:24:00,232
He's hiding something from me,
I can tell.

612
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,901
Oh, you know what? It's probably
just embarrassing family stuff.

613
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:05,195
I mean, they seem
totally bonkers.

614
00:24:05,404 --> 00:24:06,029
Yeah.

615
00:24:06,238 --> 00:24:07,030
Maybe.

616
00:24:07,572 --> 00:24:09,408
He is with
his step-mom now, so...

617
00:24:11,451 --> 00:24:12,661
So maybe...

618
00:24:13,495 --> 00:24:16,123
maybe he's not hiding
<i>something</i> from me,

619
00:24:16,915 --> 00:24:18,208
but <i>someone.</i>

620
00:24:19,376 --> 00:24:20,627
Someone who knew Chet.

621
00:24:21,128 --> 00:24:23,130
And someone I still don't trust.

622
00:24:24,005 --> 00:24:25,006
AMENADIEL:
What have you been doing?

623
00:24:25,215 --> 00:24:27,467
Oh... this and that.

624
00:24:27,884 --> 00:24:30,345
<i>This</i> being firing up
the celestial barbecue

625
00:24:30,554 --> 00:24:32,264
so <i>that</i> you can
grill another head?

626
00:24:32,472 --> 00:24:35,058
No. I just needed
to get cleaned up.

627
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:36,351
Get some air.

628
00:24:36,518 --> 00:24:38,645
I was feeling
a little claustrophobic.

629
00:24:39,604 --> 00:24:42,607
Don't you just hate
being kept in the dark?

630
00:24:44,734 --> 00:24:47,821
The good news is
you found Amenadiel.

631
00:24:48,029 --> 00:24:50,949
So we have the piece?

632
00:24:51,158 --> 00:24:52,242
Yes.

633
00:24:52,451 --> 00:24:54,536
Yes. Well, interesting
story, actually.

634
00:24:54,744 --> 00:24:55,620
Why don't you
tell her, Brother?

635
00:24:55,829 --> 00:24:57,414
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
This one's all you.

636
00:24:57,622 --> 00:24:58,999
Brother, I insist.

637
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:02,461
- Thank you.
- (chuckles softly)

638
00:25:02,669 --> 00:25:03,378
Right. Well, uh,

639
00:25:03,587 --> 00:25:05,422
upon careful
consideration,

640
00:25:05,630 --> 00:25:07,340
we've decided this whole
Flaming Sword plan

641
00:25:07,549 --> 00:25:08,550
is a crap idea.

642
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:09,676
Yes, crap.

643
00:25:09,843 --> 00:25:10,927
Mm. Have you ever considered

644
00:25:11,136 --> 00:25:13,013
finding, well,
I don't know,

645
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,389
a-a place of your own?

646
00:25:14,598 --> 00:25:16,725
Yeah. Somewhere away
from Dad, maybe?

647
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:17,559
Yes.

648
00:25:17,767 --> 00:25:19,269
LUCIFER:
Somewhere familiar,

649
00:25:19,478 --> 00:25:21,104
warmer, perhaps?

650
00:25:23,607 --> 00:25:26,735
You want...
you want me back in Hell?

651
00:25:26,943 --> 00:25:28,403
Well, not <i>in</i> Hell,
per Se,

652
00:25:28,612 --> 00:25:29,696
but in charge of Hell.

653
00:25:30,113 --> 00:25:31,323
I mean, after all,
it is a kingdom

654
00:25:31,531 --> 00:25:32,657
without a ruler.

655
00:25:33,116 --> 00:25:33,825
He is right.

656
00:25:34,034 --> 00:25:36,495
I mean, there's a great
opportunity for upward mobility.

657
00:25:37,829 --> 00:25:38,955
Lick of paint
here or there.

658
00:25:39,164 --> 00:25:40,749
The columns
would look great in white.

659
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:44,628
Beige?

660
00:25:46,963 --> 00:25:48,757
(chuckles softly)

661
00:25:48,965 --> 00:25:50,509
So it's true.

662
00:25:51,343 --> 00:25:53,178
You <i>are</i> working
against me.

663
00:25:54,095 --> 00:25:58,350
You never planned
on going with me to Heaven.

664
00:25:59,184 --> 00:25:59,809
Wait.

665
00:26:00,060 --> 00:26:01,520
How did you find out?

666
00:26:02,062 --> 00:26:04,606
Well, I persuaded...

667
00:26:05,649 --> 00:26:06,942
your little doctor.

668
00:26:07,192 --> 00:26:09,152
I'm sorry.
I had no choice.

669
00:26:09,569 --> 00:26:10,529
What did you do?

670
00:26:12,572 --> 00:26:13,198
Mum.

671
00:26:13,365 --> 00:26:14,491
AMENADIEL:
Mom.

672
00:26:14,699 --> 00:26:16,034
Listen, I understand.

673
00:26:16,243 --> 00:26:17,285
You're angry.

674
00:26:17,494 --> 00:26:20,705
Oh, I'm not angry.

675
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:23,667
Just disappointed.

676
00:26:24,709 --> 00:26:25,710
(Lucifer and Amenadiel grunt)

677
00:26:31,424 --> 00:26:32,676
(groaning)

678
00:26:35,136 --> 00:26:36,972
Give me the piece!

679
00:26:37,389 --> 00:26:38,390
No, Mom.

680
00:26:40,517 --> 00:26:42,227
You're gonna have to kill me.

681
00:26:47,399 --> 00:26:50,527
Guess I'll have to find
another way, won't I?

682
00:26:57,826 --> 00:26:59,703
Well, now look
what you've made her do.

683
00:27:00,036 --> 00:27:01,329
I've just had this tuned!

684
00:27:02,038 --> 00:27:05,041
Me? How about you
suggesting Hell

685
00:27:05,417 --> 00:27:07,669
as a retirement home? Nice.

686
00:27:07,877 --> 00:27:08,587
Maybe if you had just

687
00:27:08,795 --> 00:27:10,171
mentioned the pottery class

688
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:12,716
or water aerobics,
she would have gone for it.

689
00:27:12,924 --> 00:27:14,634
Oh, and did you have
a better idea?

690
00:27:15,635 --> 00:27:17,637
Mom's coming undone, Luci.

691
00:27:19,431 --> 00:27:20,640
- In every way.
- I know.

692
00:27:20,849 --> 00:27:22,726
And she doesn't care
who she hurts anymore.

693
00:27:24,060 --> 00:27:24,686
Linda.

694
00:27:24,894 --> 00:27:25,854
I'll go check on Linda.

695
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:27,981
You go after Mom;
she'll listen to you.

696
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,025
But, Luci, don't you dare
promise her that piece,

697
00:27:30,275 --> 00:27:31,610
because I won't
give it to her.

698
00:27:37,115 --> 00:27:40,076
♪♪♪♪

699
00:27:47,250 --> 00:27:49,002
Well, well.
Someone's clever.

700
00:27:49,961 --> 00:27:51,129
How did you get me?

701
00:27:51,338 --> 00:27:53,214
Wasn't that hard.
We tracked your phone.

702
00:27:53,715 --> 00:27:57,135
No, I mean, how did you
figure out I was the bad guy?

703
00:27:57,636 --> 00:27:59,304
Did Little Miss Dandy Lyon
tell you?

704
00:27:59,554 --> 00:28:01,014
It's over, Charlotte.
Put your hands up.

705
00:28:01,222 --> 00:28:03,266
Oh, don't worry, I'm
not going to resist.

706
00:28:04,059 --> 00:28:05,143
I'll tell you everything
you want to know.

707
00:28:05,352 --> 00:28:07,937
I just have one small request.

708
00:28:10,607 --> 00:28:12,025
(phone ringing)

709
00:28:13,526 --> 00:28:14,486
Detective.

710
00:28:14,694 --> 00:28:15,987
Any chance you've seen my Mu...

711
00:28:16,196 --> 00:28:17,489
MOM:
Looking for little ol' me?

712
00:28:17,697 --> 00:28:18,448
You were right, dear.

713
00:28:18,657 --> 00:28:21,284
Your detective
is quite good.

714
00:28:21,493 --> 00:28:22,827
(Mom chuckles)

715
00:28:23,036 --> 00:28:24,037
(whispers):
She caught me.

716
00:28:24,245 --> 00:28:25,080
Where are you?

717
00:28:25,330 --> 00:28:26,331
Santa Monica Pier.

718
00:28:26,539 --> 00:28:27,957
Such a beautiful place.

719
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,210
So many people.

720
00:28:30,585 --> 00:28:31,920
If you hurt anyone, Mum,

721
00:28:32,128 --> 00:28:33,171
if you hurt her...

722
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:35,757
And if you and your brother had
just given me what I needed.

723
00:28:35,965 --> 00:28:36,591
But who knows?

724
00:28:36,758 --> 00:28:38,593
Maybe you still can.

725
00:28:39,844 --> 00:28:40,804
Okay, that's enough.

726
00:28:41,012 --> 00:28:41,888
Mum!

727
00:28:43,807 --> 00:28:44,766
Start talking.

728
00:28:46,267 --> 00:28:47,310
Just the two of us.

729
00:28:47,519 --> 00:28:48,978
If that's all right.

730
00:28:49,354 --> 00:28:51,106
I'd rather not
put Daniel in...

731
00:28:51,898 --> 00:28:53,149
an awkward position.

732
00:28:54,859 --> 00:28:57,070
Hate to ruin all the good ones
we've been in.

733
00:28:57,570 --> 00:28:58,822
(clears throat)

734
00:28:59,072 --> 00:29:00,115
Can we go outside?

735
00:29:00,365 --> 00:29:01,241
Mm-hmm.

736
00:29:02,158 --> 00:29:03,159
I'll be fine.

737
00:29:13,253 --> 00:29:14,504
I'll miss you, Daniel.

738
00:29:15,588 --> 00:29:17,465
You are my
favorite human.

739
00:29:23,304 --> 00:29:24,597
(phone ringing)

740
00:29:24,806 --> 00:29:26,224
Hey. You find Mom?

741
00:29:26,433 --> 00:29:28,476
She's on Santa Monica Pier,
and she wants the piece.

742
00:29:28,685 --> 00:29:30,437
(horn honks, tires screech)

743
00:29:31,271 --> 00:29:33,231
We have to give it to her,
Amenadiel.

744
00:29:33,398 --> 00:29:34,733
We've run out of options.

745
00:29:35,191 --> 00:29:35,859
Please.

746
00:29:36,317 --> 00:29:37,277
Brother, please.

747
00:29:37,485 --> 00:29:40,822
She... she has Chloe.

748
00:29:45,493 --> 00:29:47,287
Linda! You here?!

749
00:29:48,121 --> 00:29:49,289
I'm tracking Lucifer's mom,

750
00:29:49,497 --> 00:29:52,459
and I think she might
be on her way.

751
00:29:55,545 --> 00:29:57,839
(groans weakly)

752
00:29:58,256 --> 00:29:58,923
Oh, no.

753
00:29:59,132 --> 00:30:00,550
No, no, no!

754
00:30:06,431 --> 00:30:07,265
Linda.

755
00:30:07,599 --> 00:30:08,850
Hey. It's okay.

756
00:30:09,058 --> 00:30:10,894
I'm here. Okay?

757
00:30:11,311 --> 00:30:12,604
You're gonna be fine.

758
00:30:16,149 --> 00:30:17,734
She did this to you, didn't she?

759
00:30:17,942 --> 00:30:21,529
(crying): She wanted to know
what Lucifer's plans were.

760
00:30:21,738 --> 00:30:23,156
I didn't want
to tell her.

761
00:30:23,364 --> 00:30:25,366
I tried to resist.
I'm so sorry.

762
00:30:25,575 --> 00:30:27,452
It's not your fault, okay?

763
00:30:27,660 --> 00:30:29,412
And you're going to be fine.

764
00:30:30,079 --> 00:30:31,122
I promise.

765
00:30:31,331 --> 00:30:32,957
I'm-I'm gonna fix you.

766
00:30:33,166 --> 00:30:33,917
Okay?

767
00:30:40,465 --> 00:30:41,466
(crying):
Help me.

768
00:30:44,511 --> 00:30:45,512
Hello, Daniel.

769
00:30:45,845 --> 00:30:46,471
Whoa!

770
00:30:46,679 --> 00:30:48,139
Whoa, whoa!

771
00:30:48,848 --> 00:30:49,724
She kissed me.

772
00:30:49,933 --> 00:30:51,142
Literally no idea
what you're talking about.

773
00:30:51,351 --> 00:30:52,101
Just get your hands up.

774
00:30:52,477 --> 00:30:53,186
No, don't be silly.

775
00:30:53,394 --> 00:30:54,813
I'm not gonna stab you.

776
00:30:54,979 --> 00:30:56,022
I'm just looking
for something.

777
00:30:56,231 --> 00:30:57,982
Come on, up. Up!

778
00:31:01,528 --> 00:31:02,529
What are you looking for?

779
00:31:03,154 --> 00:31:03,780
Uh...

780
00:31:04,072 --> 00:31:05,657
- Hello.
- Whoa.

781
00:31:06,491 --> 00:31:07,367
